<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="545" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1303,1834]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1375,1401]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Forewing length is 
<quantity box="[543,620,1375,1402]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
in the 
<typeStatus box="[695,793,1375,1401]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">holotype</typeStatus>
male. 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2021" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2021" box="[867,1129,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Cabardites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varanagara" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[867,1129,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">Cabardites varanagara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1135,1198,1375,1401]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1135,1198,1375,1401]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is the closest relative of 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2021" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2021" box="[181,311,1411,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Cabardites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tiendung" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[181,311,1411,1438]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">C. tiendung</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[317,380,1411,1437]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[317,380,1411,1437]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, from which it can be externally distinguished by the slightly less elongated forewing apex and the postmedial line being angled at costa (whereas in 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2021" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2021" box="[743,873,1447,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Cabardites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tiendung" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[743,873,1447,1474]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">C. tiendung</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[879,942,1447,1473]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[879,942,1447,1473]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
that is smoothly curved). The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2021" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2021" box="[182,347,1484,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Cabardites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varanagara" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[182,347,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">C. varanagara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[355,419,1483,1509]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[355,419,1483,1509]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2021" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2021" box="[654,785,1483,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Cabardites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tiendung" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[654,785,1483,1510]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">C. tiendung</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[793,856,1483,1509]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[793,856,1483,1509]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the valva costa being slightly more convex subbasally and less curved dorsad subapically, conspicuously shorter distal costal lobe-like process, slightly smaller distal membranous lobe of valva, slightly narrower distal section of sacculus, distal diverticulum of aedeagus vesica bearing two slightly shorter robust blade-like cornuti and one small spine (whereas in 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2021" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2021" box="[1123,1255,1591,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Cabardites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tiendung" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1123,1255,1591,1618]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">C. tiendung</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1262,1326,1591,1617]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1262,1326,1591,1617]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
the distal diverticulum bears three robust blade-like cornuti, which are slightly longer), and conspicuously broader medial cluster of short but robust spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1303,1834]" box="[199,426,1699,1725]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">Female is unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
