<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="545" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1303,1834]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1771,1797]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">Etymology</emphasis>
. Varanagara was the capital of the kingdom created by Paña Thera Taeng in the territory of the current 
<collectingRegion box="[202,355,1807,1834]" country="Thailand" name="Nan" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">Nan Province</collectingRegion>
in the XIIIth century.
</paragraph>
